				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Just to help us understand your problem: Is the address you have found a RAM address ($0000-$07FF or $6000-$7FFF) or a ROM address ($8000 or higher)?<br /><br /><ul><li>If it is a RAM address, the problem is that the program is overwriting it every time a game starts. Find the ROM address that initializes it.</li><li>If it is a ROM address, the problem is that you have modified a copy of the ROM file loaded into the emulator but haven't written the modified ROM file back to disk under a new name so that you can prepare an IPS. </li></ul></div>

