				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Set a write breakpoint on $037E to see if you can find the piece of code in ROM that initially sets the continue count. Once the debugger stops, the piece of code will probably look a little like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; lda #$03<br />&nbsp; sta $037e&nbsp; ; Execution paused here</div><br /><br />Change that $03 to a $01, and you have a ROM cheat that you can use instead of the RAM cheat.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

